'''Little George Coc<nowiki>'</nowiki>nuts''' is a valley on the southwestern end of [[Pitcairn Island]]. It got its name from a [[coconut]] grove which was once maintained there by George Young, son of Pitcairn settler and [[HMS Bounty|HMS ''Bounty'']] mutineer [[Ned Young]].

